shortdesc.ph: Indicates the error codes for the call result.

plentry.pd: (1): Token renewal failed due to an unknown server error. Check the parameters used to generate the token, regenerate the token, and retry .
(1): Token renewal failed due to an unknown server error. Check the parameters used to generate the token, regenerate the token, and retry calling .
(2): Token renewal failed because the provided token has expired. Generate a new token with a longer expiration time and retry .

(3): Token renewal failed because the token is invalid. Common causes include:
The App Certificate is enabled in the Agora Console, but the channel is joined without using a token. When the App Certificate is enabled, you must use a token to join the channel.
The specified in joinChannel does not match the used when generating the token.
The channel name specified in joinChannel does not match the channel name used when generating the token.

(3): Token renewal failed because the token is invalid. Common causes include: the App Certificate is enabled in the Agora Console but the channel is joined without using a token; the specified in the joinChannel method does not match the used when generating the token; the channel name specified in the joinChannel method does not match the channel name used when generating the token.
(4): Token renewal failed due to an invalid channel name. Check the channel name, generate a new token, and retry .
(4): Token renewal failed due to an invalid channel name. Check the channel name, generate a new token, and retry calling .
(5): Token renewal failed because the App ID in the token does not match the current App ID. Check the App ID, generate a new token, and retry .
(5): Token renewal failed because the App ID in the token does not match the current App ID. Check the App ID, generate a new token, and retry calling .
(6): The previous token renewal request was canceled due to a new request being initiated.
